      {
        "id": 30642,
        "title": {
          "romaji": "Vinland Saga",
          "english": "Vinland Saga",
          "native": "ヴィンランド・サガ"
        },
        "coverImage": {
          "large": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/medium/bx30642-0mjRDkf4THpo.jpg"
        },
        "description": "As a child, Thorfinn sat at the feet of the great Leif Ericson and thrilled to wild tales of a land far to the west. But his youthful fantasies were shattered by a mercenary raid. Raised by the Vikings who murdered his father, Thorfinn became a terrifying warrior, forever seeking to kill the band's leader, Askeladd, and avenge his father. Sustaining Thorfinn through his ordeal are his pride in his family and his dreams of a fertile westward land, a land without war or slavery … the land Leif called Vinland.\n<br><br>\n(Source: Kodansha USA)\n<br><br>\n<i>Notes:<br>\n- Won the Grand Prize at the Japan Media Arts Festival in 2009.<br>\n- Winner of the 36th Kodansha Manga Award in the General category in 2012.</i>",
